November 10, 2019 With v0.24.0, WTF now has better support for theme-like colour settings. It&rsquo;s far from perfect, a lot of modules will have to be improved internally to make theming ubiquitous, but it&rsquo;s a start.
By way of example, if you&rsquo;re running v0.24 or later, drop this into your config at the top, replace your existing colors: YAML block with the following and you&rsquo;ll end up with a facsimile of an old-school green monochrome monitor display (you may need to restart WTF to get changes to take effect).
Copy   colors: background: &#34;transparent&#34; border: focusable: &#34;lightgreen&#34; focused: &#34;goldenrod&#34; normal: &#34;darkgreen&#34; checked: &#34;gray&#34; highlight: fore: &#34;black&#34; back: &#34;green&#34; labels: &#34;lightgreen::b&#34; rows: even: &#34;green&#34; odd: &#34;lightgreen&#34; subheading: &#34;lightgreen::b&#34; text: &#34;green&#34; title: &#34;lightgreen&#34;
